{
  "texts": [
    "First, TcCSE expression could precede caffeic acid accumulation.",
    "The fact that the TcCSE overexpression experiment (Fig. 4B) was collected 8 h post inoculation may not have provided sufficient time for metabolite accumulation.",
    "Second, it could be the case that caffeic acid was converted into lignin via sinapic acid [134], which would not be detected using our metabolite extraction protocol.",
    "And lastly, caffeic acid could have been converted into one or more caffeic acid derivatives that are difficult to predict and quantify [127].",
    "Together, our results indicate that TcCSE and caffeic acid are potentially important components of the cacao plant defense, though we so far lack a complete understanding of expression time course and the fate of resulting metabolites."
  ]
}